org.waarp.openr66.client

Class MultipleDirectTransfer

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.waarp.openr66.client.AbstractTransfer
      • org.waarp.openr66.client.DirectTransfer
        • org.waarp.openr66.client.MultipleDirectTransfer
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Runnable

    public class MultipleDirectTransfer
extends DirectTransfer
    Direct Transfer from a client with or without database connection to transfer for multiple files to multiple hosts at once.
    Files will have to be separated by ','.
    Hosts will have to be separated by ','.

    For instance: -to host1,host2,host3 -file file1,file2
    Will generate:
    -to host1 -file file1
    -to host1 -file file2
    -to host2 -file file1
    -to host2 -file file2
    -to host3 -file file1
    -to host3 -file file2
